本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:陳敬予研究生(外文):Jing-Yu Chen論文名稱:模糊賽局運用於高鐵、鐵路、航空競爭策略選擇之研究論文名稱(外文):A study of Fuzzy Game Theory Applied in Selection of Competition Strategy for High-Speed Rail, Railway, and Air lines.指導教授:張炳騰指導教授(外文):Ping-Teng Chang學位類別:碩士校院名稱:東海大學系所名稱:工業工程與經營資訊學系學門:工程學門學類:工業工程學類論文出版年:2007畢業學年度:95語文別:中文論文頁數:111中文關鍵詞:SWOT分析、非合作模糊賽局、模糊線性規劃、層級分析法外文關鍵詞:SWOT、fuzzy non-cooperation game、AHP、fuzzy linear programming model相關次數:

被引用:2點閱:656評分:下載:158書目收藏:6



自從政府政策確定台灣高鐵要加入台灣西部長途運輸市場，陸續有許多關於高鐵與受到高鐵影響的交通工具各方面的研究相繼提出，但始終僅站在各交通工具的角度來分析探討，並未考量在競爭的環境下，客觀考慮策略的重要性並結合影響策略的因素來決定及比較分析適合各交通工具的策略。所以，本研究提出結合質性與量性的方法，發展出在競爭環境下策略選擇的架構，從質性與量性的方法下之綜合評論，對於高鐵、台鐵與航空做策略建議與分析。本研究首先參考過去文獻來瞭解高鐵、台鐵與航空的現況與高鐵加入後的影響，再根據各交通工具其不同運輸市場及經營環境條件與特性，以承載率為主要考量，來重新修正與建立SWOT分析及策略發展。再根據此SWOT分析所發展的策略結合層級分析法，提供給決策除了SWOT分析之外，於客觀意見下必須優先考量之策略及建議。接著利用的AHP方法來決定各策略考量搭乘意願因素後的權重，並將此權重帶入多人多屬性非合作模糊賽局，上述的非合作模糊賽局是以主觀的認定屬性值，本研究採用AHP客觀的屬性值代入，再以模糊線性規劃模式求解，探討最大承載率為目標及競爭環境下，高鐵、台鐵與航空可求得之最大報酬與最佳策略，並與客觀意見下的策略權重一起探討，最後給予各交通工具建議策略與分析，整理如下:高鐵建議策略:SO策略—員工服務訓練、旅遊主題套餐、專業人性化設備，ST策略—發展國際性品牌，WO策略—與台鐵軌道系統整合、開發高鐵商圈、網路訂票系統、旅遊優惠活動，WT策略—加強行車安全、彈性票價系統。台鐵建議策略:SO策略—鐵路捷運化、旅遊主題套餐，ST策略—與高鐵系統整合、票務自動化系統，WO策略—彈性票價系統、改善行車排班，WT策略—車廂清潔舒適、增加餐點樣式、加強行車安全、員工服務訓練。航空建議策略:SO策略—開發購票通路、旅遊主題套餐、員工服務訓練、套裝旅遊廣告，ST策略—重新規劃班次，WO策略—旅遊優惠活動、與其他交通產業合作、加強訂票系統，WT策略—彈性票價系統。

Since the government's policy toward the Taiwan high-speed railway to join the long-distance transportation market in western Taiwan. There are many of  studies by high-speed rail and the other transports affect in high-speed rail. But all transports always the only means of transport from the perspective to analyze, never consider in a competitive environment. Strategy objective consideration of the importance and impact of combining strategy and decision factors for the comparative analysis of the transport strategy. This study combined qualitative and quantitative methods used in the high-speed rail, railway,and Air lines in a competitive environment under the strategic option from the qualitative and quantitative methods under the Comprehensive comment, the high-speed rail, railway,and Air lines  do with the Strategy and Analysis.The first reference to the literature to understand the status of the high-speed rail, railway,and Air lines and the impact after high-speed rail joining. According the different transport modes of its market and operating conditions and characteristics to the main load-bearing rate considerations, and according to the high-speed rail of the official opening of the current situation, To re-establish that SWOT analysis and strategy development. According SWOT analysis of this development strategy with AHP, AHP using the method to determine the strategy weights, in addition to the decision-making SWOT analysis, views on the objective must be the top priority strategies and recommendations. Then the option will fare, use AHP method to determine the strategic consideration factors will take the weight. This will bring the weights fuzzy non-cooperation game, the above-mentioned non-cooperation fuzzy game based on subjective value of the properties identified. This study used AHP objective value of the property on behalf of income, then use fuzzy linear programming model in solution. Discussion of the largest bearing objectives and competitive environment, the high-speed rail, railway and Air lines can be obtained with the greatest reward and the best strategy with the objective views of the strategy to explore weight, but to give the proposed transport strategy and analysis.Proposed high-speed rail strategy : SO Strategy—Staff training services, Tourism theme packages, Humanity professional equipment; ST Strategy—Development of international brands; WO Strategy—With the Taiwan Railway track systems integration, development of high iron market area, Internet booking systems, travel offers activities; WT Strategy —improving road safety, flexible fares.Proposed railway strategy : SO Strategy—MRT railway, a tourism-themed packages; ST Strategy—With the high-speed railway system integration, automated ticketing system; WO Strategy—Flexible fare system and improve traffic scheduling; WT Strategy—Clean and comfortable compartment, increased meal patterns, improving road safety, staff training services. Proposed railway strategy : SO Strategy—Purchase of development paths, a tourism-themed packages, service staff training, advertising tours; ST Strategy—Re-planning services; WO Strategy—Travel offers activities, With the other transport industries, strengthen cooperation in booking system; WT Strategy—Flexible fare system.

